# Mozilla CA Certificate Bundle
# Source: https://curl.se/ca/cacert.pem
#
# To populate this file, run:
#   curl -o data/cacert.pem https://curl.se/ca/cacert.pem
#
# This file is uploaded to SPIFFS (the 'data/' partition) and is NOT used
# directly by esp_http_client in the current firmware build — TLS is handled
# by the ESP-IDF built-in certificate bundle (esp_crt_bundle_attach) which
# is compiled into the firmware image.  This stub file is kept here as a
# reference and for future use if a custom PEM bundle is preferred over the
# IDF built-in bundle.
#
# If you want to use this file instead of the built-in bundle, edit
# net_bridge.cpp: replace `.crt_bundle_attach = esp_crt_bundle_attach`
# with a custom esp_tls_t config that loads the PEM from SPIFFS.
